[anchor|#section_own_yjf_l1b] In Acumatica ERP, you can fulfill a sales order even if some of the items on the sales order have no ''Available'' quantity at the warehouse. You can allocate these items at a warehouse that differs from the warehouse of the sales order and then transfer the allocated items to fulfill the sales order, as described in this guide.{br}{TOC}[anchor|#section_xwm_511_dy][anchor|#title_tcs_r1c_n1b] ==1. Create a Sales Order== On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, you create a sales order of the ''SO'' type and fill in the '''Document Details''' tab with the ordered items.{br}
If some items have no ''Available'' quantity at the warehouse of the sales order line, as shown in the following screenshot with ''LAPTOP12'', you can allocate them at another warehouse.((({S:Hint}You can select ''Ship Complete'' as the '''Shipping Rule''' of each sales order line if you want to ship the sales order only if the full quantity of all the sales order lines is available for shipping at the warehouse specified in the lines. You can predefine each customer&rsquo;s default shipping rule for sales orders on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_30_00|Customers] ([~/?ScreenId=AR303000|AR303000]) form. )))[anchor|#fig_y2h_hpg_11b][anchor|#image_cgh_hpg_11b][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__SO_Transfer1.png|popup|450px] For details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__How_Create_Sale_Order|To Create a Sales Order (SO)].[anchor|#section_j2v_5tl_l1b][anchor|#title_xw5_r1c_n1b] ==2. Allocate the Unavailable Quantities of the Sales Order Lines== On the '''Document Details''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, you allocate the items that have insufficient ''Available'' quantity at the warehouse. In the '''Allocations''' dialog box (as the screenshot below shows), you select the '''Allocated''' check box and an '''Alloc. Warehouse''' that differs from the warehouse of the sales order line and for which the item has a sufficient ''Available'' quantity.{br}
When you save the sales order with the ''Open'' status (that is, with the '''Hold''' check box cleared), the system generates transfer requests for each line of the sales order for which the item has been allocated in a warehouse other than the warehouse selected in the line.[anchor|#fig_mb5_jvc_n1b][anchor|#image_gc5_jvc_n1b][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__SO_Transfer2.png|popup|450px] For details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__How_Allocate_Item|To Reserve an Inventory Item for an Order].[anchor|#section_fhy_5tl_l1b][anchor|#title_dyx_r1c_n1b] ==3. Create the Transfer Order== On the toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, you click '''Actions''' > '''Create Transfer Order''' to create transfer orders. On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_90_00|Create Transfer Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO509000|SO509000]) form, which opens, you process the transfer requests of the sales order (see the following screenshot).((({S:Hint}You can also create transfer orders for multiple sales orders if the '''Order Type''' and '''Order Nbr.''' are cleared on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_90_00|Create Transfer Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO509000|SO509000]) form. ))) The system creates a consolidated transfer order, which is a sales order of the ''TR'' type, for each group of transfer requests that have both the same source warehouse ('''From Warehouse''') and the same destination warehouse ('''To Warehouse'''). The date of the created transfer orders is that specified in the '''Creation Date''' box.[anchor|#fig_c2t_xgd_n1b][anchor|#image_qft_xgd_n1b][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__SO_Transfer3.png|popup|450px]((({S:Hint}If you want to ship the transfer order only in full, you can select ''Ship Complete'' as the '''Shipping Rule''' of each transfer order line to avoid a partial shipment. You can predefine each branch&rsquo;s default shipping rule for transfer orders on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_20_00|Branches] ([~/?ScreenId=CS102000|CS102000]) form. ))) For details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__How_Create_Transfer_Order|To Create a Transfer Order (TR)].[anchor|#section_hx1_vtl_l1b][anchor|#title_jk1_s1c_n1b] ==4. Create the Shipment for the Transfer Order== On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, you create the shipment for each transfer order (that is, sales order of the ''TR'' type) that has been created, as the following screenshot shows.((({S:Hint}You can also create shipments for multiple transfer orders on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_10_00|Process Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO501000|SO501000]) form by selecting the ''Create Shipment'' action and processing the needed orders. )))[anchor|#fig_dhc_4zd_n1b][anchor|#image_h3c_4zd_n1b][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__SO_Transfer4.png|popup|450px] For details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__How_Create_Shipment|To Create a Shipment for an Order].[anchor|#section_owr_k12_n1b][anchor|#title_xqj_h12_n1b] ==5. Process the Shipment== On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302000|SO302000]) form, by selecting the appropriate actions on the form toolbar, you confirm each shipment that has been created and update the inventory to issue the items, as the following screenshot shows.((({S:Hint}You can also process multiple shipments at once on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_30_00|Process Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO503000|SO503000]) form. )))[anchor|#fig_lfv_4zd_n1b][anchor|#image_zgv_4zd_n1b][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__SO_Transfer5.png|popup|450px] For details, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__How_Confirm_Shipment|To Confirm a Shipment].[anchor|#section_fb2_vtl_l1b][anchor|#title_ozc_s1c_n1b] ==6. Create and Process the Transfer Receipts for the Shipment== On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form, you create a receipt of the ''Transfer Receipt'' type, as the screenshot below shows. In the '''Warehouse''' box in the Summary area, you select the warehouse of the sales order, which will receive the transfer order.{br}
You then release the transfer receipt, which causes the inventory receipt to be created. When this inventory receipt is released, the system counts the items that have been transferred to the sales order as available.((({S:Hint}You can also receive multiple transfer orders with one transfer receipt. )))[anchor|#fig_mbm_1d2_n1b][anchor|#image_adm_1d2_n1b][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__SO_Transfer6.png|popup|450px][anchor|#related-links_mqs_yjf_l1b] ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__MNG_TR_Orders|Sale with Transferred Stock Items] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_scn_Sale_with_Transfer|Processing Steps for a Sale with Transfer]
